The sum function is the sum of digits of a number. So for a given number, sum its digits until it's less than 10. Wait, the sum function in Java:

public static int sum(int a) {
    int ans =0;
    while (a >=10) {
        ans += a%10;
        a = a/10;
    }
    ans +=a;
    return ans;
} Wait, that's not exactly sum of all digits.
